column1: ITB 25-071 Addendum 1 (Fire Station No. 6 Pavement and Storm System Rehab),"Fire Station No. 6 Pavement and Storm System Rehab","ITB","City of College Station","Issued","COCS - Invitation to Bid - Electronic","5/21/2025","5/21/2025 12:00:05 PM (CT)","6/26/2025 02:00:00 PM (CT)","6/26/2025 02:00:00 PM (CT)","6/19/2025 02:00:00 PM (CT)","4 days 16 hours 35 minutes 11 seconds","","Estimated Project Amount $60,000.00

The City of College Station invites qualified contractors to submit bids for Soil densification and concrete leveling with high density polyurethane foam, expansion joint re-sealing, cleaning of existing 36” storm pipe, and detention pond outfall control structure replacement.

A Pre-bid Meeting will be held at College Station Fire Department: Station 6, located at 610 University Dr E. College Station, Texas and via Teams on Thursday, June 5, 2025, at 2:00 p.m. CT. This meeting is not mandatory, but attendance is highly recommended. Site visit to follow.","Login

column10: ITB 25-071 Addendum 1 (Fire Station No. 6 Pavement and Storm System Rehab)

column1: The City of College Station invites qualified contractors to submit bids for Soil densification and concrete leveling with high density polyurethane foam, expansion joint re-sealing, cleaning of existing 36” storm pipe, and detention pond outfall control structure replacement.

A Pre-bid Meeting will be held at College Station Fire Department: Station 6, located at 610 University Dr E. College Station, Texas and via Teams on Thursday, June 5, 2025, at 2:00 p.m. CT. This meeting is not mandatory, but attendance is highly recommended. Site visit to follow.

column10: 25-0039-A Addendum 1 (Annual Contract for Installation of Granular Activated Carbon)

The San Jacinto River Authority seeks to enter into an Agreement with a qualified Firm or Corporation (Respondent) with substantial and relevant experience and expertise to provide the services of ongoing maintenance to remove used media of Granular Activated Carbon (GAC) and replace with newly manufactured or regenerated GAC, refer to Scope of Work in Exhibit A.

City of Bryan 2-Dimensional Stormwater Model Update & Preparation of a Master Drainage Plan

The City of Bryan, Texas is requesting qualifications for Engineering services from firms interested in contracting with the City to expand and update the City’s existing 2-D Stormwater Model and utilize it to prepare a Master Drainage Plan that outlines improvements to the City’s stormwater systems through future community flood mitigation projects that benefit NFIP insured properties within the City limits. The purpose of the Request for Qualifications (RFQ) process is to identify the most qualified firm.","Login

column1: City of Bryan 2-Dimensional Stormwater Model Update & Preparation of a Master Drainage Plan

The City of Bryan, Texas is requesting qualifications for Engineering services from firms interested in contracting with the City to expand and update the City’s existing 2-D Stormwater Model and utilize it to prepare a Master Drainage Plan that outlines improvements to the City’s stormwater systems through future community flood mitigation projects that benefit NFIP insured properties within the City limits. The purpose of the Request for Qualifications (RFQ) process is to identify the most qualified firm.
